tudent-shell`, `risk-explorer`, and preferences | `#/admin/faculties/:.../batches/:...` is the canonical proof route; `#/admin/history` is the hidden-records surface; search can route into students, faculty, and requests without using the visible tabs | `SystemAdminSessionBoundary` blocks the workspace unless the active session role is `SYSTEM_ADMIN`, even if the user is logged in under another grant. |\\naudit-map/15-final-maps/role-feature-matrix.md:20:- `canAccessPage()` is a client-side gate only. It keeps the academic router from staying on a disallowed page, but it does not replace backend auth.\\naudit-map/15-final-maps/role-feature-matrix.md:23:- `requireRole()` is the first backend gate on the protected routes. It checks the active grant only.\\naudit-map/15-final-maps/role-feature-matrix.md:32:- `student-history`, `student-shell`, and `risk-explorer` are cross-cutting routes reached from student cards, mentee cards, queue rows, and proof controls.\\naudit-map/15-final-maps/role-feature-matrix.md:33:- `unlock-review` is reachable from queue actions and direct hashes, even though it is not a top-level sidebar item.\\naudit-map/15-final-maps/role-feature-matrix.md:34:- `#/admin/proof-dashboard` and the canonical proof hierarchy route are route-level entry points, not visible top tabs.\\naudit-map/15-final-maps/role-feature-matrix.md:35:- `#/admin/history` is a hidden-records workspace, but admin search can still surface requests from that section.\\naudit-map/15-final-maps/role-feature-matrix.md:43:- `student-shell` and `risk-explorer` are easy to reach indirectly, but their server-side scope checks are stricter than the route names imply.\\naudit-map/15-final-maps/feature-registry.md:7:| Public portal chooser and hash routing | Bootstrap / portal entry | `src/App.tsx`, `src/portal-entry.tsx`, `src/portal-routing.ts` | [`04-feature-atoms/public-portal-chooser-and-routing.md`](../04-feature-atoms/public-portal-chooser-and-routing.md) |\\naudit-map/15-final-map